</think>
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{A}\mathbf{A}^T &= \begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} a & c \\ b & d \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} a^2 + b^2 & ac + bd \\ ac + bd & c^2 + d^2 \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
For $\mathbf{A}\mathbf{A}^T = \mathbf{I},$ we need:
\begin{align*}
a^2 + b^2 &= 1 \\
c^2 + d^2 &= 1 \\
ac + bd &= 0
\end{align*}
</think>
Adding all the leftsätze><content> terms in the above equations yields $a^2 + b^2 + c^2 + d^2 = 2.$</content><intסתר> Thus, the answer is $\boxed{2}.$</ userID>

